---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="Terms of Service - Glenbrook Heating & Air Conditioning"
  description="Terms of service for Glenbrook Heating & Air Conditioning. Review our service terms, conditions, and policies."
>
  <Header />
  
  <main>
    <!-- Hero Section -->
    <section class="pt-24 pb-16 bg-gradient-to-br from-primary-900 to-primary-700 text-white">
      <div class="container-custom">
        <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto text-center">
          <h1 class="text-5xl md:text-6xl font-bold mb-6">
            Terms of <span class="text-primary-200">Service</span>
          </h1>
          <p class="text-xl md:text-2xl text-primary-100">
            Please review our terms and conditions for HVAC services and website usage.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Terms Content -->
    <section class="section-padding bg-white">
      <div class="container-custom">
        <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto prose prose-lg">
          <p class="text-gray-600 mb-8">
            <strong>Last updated:</strong> January 1, 2024
          </p>
          
          <h2>Acceptance of Terms</h2>
          <p>
            By using our website or engaging our HVAC services, you agree to be bound by these Terms of Service. If you do not agree to these terms, please do not use our services.
          </p>
          
          <h2>Service Description</h2>
          <p>
            Glenbrook Heating & Air Conditioning provides residential and commercial HVAC services including:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Heating and cooling system installation</li>
            <li>HVAC repair and maintenance</li>
            <li>Emergency HVAC services</li>
            <li>Indoor air quality solutions</li>
            <li>System inspections and consultations</li>
          </ul>
          
          <h2>Scheduling and Appointments</h2>
          <p>
            Service appointments are scheduled based on availability. We will make reasonable efforts to arrive within the scheduled time window. Delays may occur due to weather, traffic, or emergency service calls.
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Appointment confirmations will be provided via phone, email, or text</li>
            <li>Cancellations must be made at least 24 hours in advance</li>
            <li>Emergency services are available 24/7 with additional charges</li>
          </ul>
          
          <h2>Pricing and Payment</h2>
          <p>
            Service pricing is based on current rates and may vary depending on:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Type and complexity of work required</li>
            <li>Parts and materials needed</li>
            <li>Time of service (emergency rates apply after hours)</li>
            <li>Travel distance for service calls</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            Payment is due upon completion of services unless other arrangements have been made. We accept cash, check, and major credit cards.
          </p>
          
          <h2>Estimates and Quotes</h2>
          <p>
            Free estimates are provided for installation and replacement projects. Repair estimates may require a diagnostic fee, which will be applied toward the cost of repairs if you choose to proceed.
          </p>
          
          <h2>Warranties</h2>
          <p>
            We provide warranties on our workmanship and installed equipment:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Labor Warranty:</strong> 1 year on all installation and repair work</li>
            <li><strong>Equipment Warranty:</strong> Manufacturer warranties apply to all new equipment</li>
            <li><strong>Parts Warranty:</strong> 90 days on replacement parts</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            Warranties do not cover damage due to misuse, neglect, or normal wear and tear.
          </p>
          
          <h2>Limitation of Liability</h2>
          <p>
            Our liability is limited to the cost of the services performed. We are not responsible for:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Indirect, incidental, or consequential damages</li>
            <li>Damage to personal property not directly caused by our negligence</li>
            <li>Delays in service due to circumstances beyond our control</li>
            <li>Pre-existing conditions or code violations</li>
          </ul>
          
          <h2>Customer Responsibilities</h2>
          <p>
            Customers are responsible for:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Providing safe and clear access to HVAC equipment</li>
            <li>Disclosing known issues or hazards</li>
            <li>Ensuring pets are secured during service visits</li>
            <li>Maintaining systems according to manufacturer recommendations</li>
          </ul>
          
          <h2>Permits and Codes</h2>
          <p>
            When required, we will obtain necessary permits for installation work. All work will be performed in accordance with local building codes and regulations. Additional costs may apply for permit fees and inspections.
          </p>
          
          <h2>Dispute Resolution</h2>
          <p>
            Any disputes arising from our services will be resolved through:
          </p>
          <ol>
            <li>Direct communication with our management team</li>
            <li>Mediation through a mutually agreed upon mediator</li>
            <li>Binding arbitration if mediation is unsuccessful</li>
          </ol>
          
          <h2>Website Usage</h2>
          <p>
            Our website is provided for informational purposes. You may not:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Use the site for any unlawful purpose</li>
            <li>Attempt to gain unauthorized access to our systems</li>
            <li>Transmit viruses or malicious code</li>
            <li>Copy or reproduce content without permission</li>
          </ul>
          
          <h2>Modifications to Terms</h2>
          <p>
            We reserve the right to modify these terms at any time. Changes will be posted on our website with an updated effective date. Continued use of our services constitutes acceptance of modified terms.
          </p>
          
          <h2>Contact Information</h2>
          <p>
            For questions about these terms or our services, please contact us:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Phone:</strong> (555) HVAC-PRO</li>
            <li><strong>Email:</strong> info@glenbrookheating.com</li>
            <li><strong>Address:</strong> [Your Business Address]</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
  
  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
  .prose {
    color: #374151;
    max-width: none;
  }
  
  .prose h2 {
    color: #111827;
    font-size: 1.875rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-top: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }
  
  .prose p {
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
  }
  
  .prose ul, .prose ol {
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
  }
  
  .prose li {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }
  
  .prose strong {
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #111827;
  }
</style>